<h1><i>Apple Cake Recipe</i></h1>
<br>
<p>This Moist Apple Pecan Cake is so delicious!</p>
<p>This apple pecan cinnamon cake is so soft and fluffy,a little sticky on top
    (like a caramel candy) and very tasty with light crunchiness of pecan nuts and little tartness of apples.</p>

<br>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ol>
    <li>150 gms sugar +115 gms Palm sugar or Brown sugar</li>
    <li>2 Eggs</li>
    <li>225 gms All purpose flour</li>
    <li>200 gms Softened Butter</li>
    <li>1 tsp baking powder</li>
    <li>1 tsp cinnamon powder</li>
    <li>1/4 tsp salt</li>
    <li>1 tsps vanilla essence</li>
    <li>2 Granny Smith apples, peeled and chopped in small pieces</li>
    <li>90-100 gms pecans, chopped small</li>
</ol>

<h2>How to make the Apple cake</h2>
<p>We can prepare the cake batter in these simple steps</p>
<ul>
    <li>Cream the butter and sugar</li>
    <li>Add eggs one by one</li>
    <li>Add the vanilla extract</li>
    <li>Sift in the flour baking powder and salt and combine everything until they are just combined into a homogenous mixture.</li>
    <li>Transfer into a greased baking tray.</li>
    <li>Add the apple,pecan and palm sugar or brown sugar on top.
        (or if don't like the rustic top part of cake you can keep some cake batter to add on the top).</li>
    <li>Using a skewer,swirl the top of cake to get marble effect.</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3>Baking the cake</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Bake at 375 F Preheated oven for 60-80 minutes.</li>
    <li>You can check the doneness of cake, by poking a skewer into the center of the cake and if comes out clean, our cake is done.</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h4><b><i>Enjoy!</i></b></h4>

